&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Director, Beauty&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dynamic Account Director to help lead 5W&#39;s expanding Beauty practice. This is an exciting opportunity for an individual eager to grow their career with a diverse range of clients, with a focus on Beauty communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal individual will have worked with a diverse roster of consumer clients within an agency setting, is an expert at pitching, and possesses superior account and time management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team&#39;s top priority is hiring an Account Director who brings a strong blend of influencer expertise, digital creative strategy, and a deep understanding of pop culture — someone who can identify emerging trends, translate them into smart, culturally relevant recommendations, and lead integrated campaigns across earned and influencer channels. While influencer leadership and creative strategy are the primary focus, it&#39;s equally important that this person has strong media relations experience and can develop and drive a thoughtful earned media strategy that complements the broader communications approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here&#39;s what you&#39;ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as primary contact to clients, continually fostering client-agency relationship to build trust and become a valuable resource and counselor to clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead integrated campaigns across earned and influencer channels, ensuring both work together to support the broader communications approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify emerging trends and pop culture moments and translate them into smart, culturally relevant recommendations for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of the emerging world of AI, exploring how new tools and technologies can enhance creative strategy, media outreach, and campaign execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and implement strategic communications programming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and drive thoughtful earned media strategies that complement influencer and digital creative efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute creative campaigns, brand partnerships, and influencer programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and delegate responsibilities of daily workflow of multiple accounts while driving consistent media results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate account status to agency management regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate proficiency in writing and editing materials, particularly presentations, program plans, and media strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic guidance to clients and team members on an ongoing basis; anticipate and address clients&#39; needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot media, team, or strategy problems as they arise; seek senior management input when appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motivate team members by promptly reviewing work and providing constructive feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strive to develop the best communication and presentation skills possible to effectively articulate ideas to clients, colleagues, and others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct and lead monthly conference calls and meetings with clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain relationships with influential members of the media, influencers, and their agents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance and leadership to team members on effective pitching, team issues, account workflow, and general account issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the development of materials for new business opportunities including timelines, proposals, business decks, and case studies; assist in generating new business leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in brainstorming sessions to develop strategic/creative thinking for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Misc. research, duties, and projects as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here&#39;s what you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B.S/B.A in P

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief AI Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5W Public Relations is building a standalone AI Communications practice — with its own P&amp;amp;L, product suite, and market position. This is not a title inside an existing org. It is a practice to build from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LLMs are reshaping how brands are perceived. Citations in AI outputs are the new search ranking. Generative Engine Optimization is an emerging discipline with no established leader. This role exists to make 5W that leader — and to build the revenue engine behind it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Productize GEO and Citation Share into three priced offerings with defined SOWs and a recurring revenue structure — within the first 90 days.&lt;br&gt;• Close five enterprise pilots at $250K+ each and build the pipeline behind them.&lt;br&gt;• Build the AI Communications org — drawing from 5W&#39;s existing talent and external hires you recruit directly.&lt;br&gt;• Own the public narrative for the practice: keynotes, earned media, podcasts, and LLM citation presence.&lt;br&gt;• Co-own the category story with firm leadership across all client-facing and market-facing channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE&#39;RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proven track record building or scaling an AI-native or martech business to $10M–$100M in revenue. An exit is a plus.&lt;br&gt;• Direct experience selling AI, data, or measurement products into Fortune 500 marketing organizations — to CMOs and CEOs, not intermediaries.&lt;br&gt;• Demonstrated ability to package services into productized, recurring-revenue offerings.&lt;br&gt;• Technical fluency in LLMs, retrieval, embeddings, and GEO mechanics — enough to be credible with both clients and builders.&lt;br&gt;• Experience as a public-facing operator: conference stages, media appearances, thought leadership that generates inbound.&lt;br&gt;• A network of brand-side CMOs, CCOs, and Heads of Growth — not agency-side relationships.&lt;br&gt;• Founder or P&amp;amp;L ownership experience. You build teams and carry numbers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Minimum 8 years of experience in revenue-generating roles at AI, SaaS, or data companies.&lt;br&gt;• At least one example of closing six- or seven-figure deals with enterprise brand-side buyers.&lt;br&gt;• Ability to travel to clients. Role is hub-agnostic; preferred locations include Miami, Tampa, Austin, London, Lisbon, or Singapore.&lt;br&gt;• Must be based outside the New York metro area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THIS ROLE IS &lt;em&gt;NOT &lt;/em&gt;FOR YOU IF&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Your background is primarily agency-side — PR firms, holding companies, or innovation titles without P&amp;amp;L ownership.&lt;br&gt;• Your last three roles were VP-level positions inside large agencies with no independent revenue responsibility.&lt;br&gt;• You are a researcher or academic without commercial operating experience.&lt;br&gt;• You are looking for a title, a team to manage, and a defined playbook. This role requires building all three.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Growth Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About 5W&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5W is the AI Communications Firm, helping brands build authority across the platforms where decisions now happen — ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews — alongside earned media, digital, and influencer channels. We combine public relations, digital marketing, Generative Engine Optimization (GEO), and proprietary AI visibility research to help clients measure and grow their presence in AI-driven buyer research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded more than 20 years ago, 5W has been recognized as a top U.S. PR agency by O&#39;Dwyer&#39;s, named Agency of the Year in the American Business Awards®, Top Place to Work in Communications 2026 by Ragan, and a Digiday WorkLife Employer of the Year. We serve clients across B2C, B2B, Public Affairs, Crisis Communications, and Digital Marketing. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.5wpr.com&quot;&gt;www.5wpr.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5W is looking for a Chief Growth Officer to own new revenue and build the pipeline that takes us from a top U.S. PR agency to the category-defining AI Communications Firm. This is an executive-level commercial leadership role with a clear Year 1 mandate: close $10M+ in new ARR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New business pipeline across PR, GEO, AI visibility, digital, influencer, and crisis practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outbound BD team and inbound conversion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing strategy and packaging for the AI service line ($25–75K/mo retainers, $1M+ anchor accounts)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-sell motion across the existing client book — every client buys at least two practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner channel development: martech, AI platforms, and holding company referrals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal closer presence on every deal $500K+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Year 1 Targets&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$10M+ in new ARR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 anchor clients at $1M+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;60% measurement/analytics attach rate on retainers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Average deal size up 40%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years selling services at $1M+ deal sizes — agency, consulting, or martech&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience building and running a BD organization, not just carrying a number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in how AI is reshaping buyer research — ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini, Google AI Overviews — and the ability to sell into CMOs and General Counsel without a deck crutch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record beats pedigree. Show us the number.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Assistant to Executive— Part-Time, Mostly Remote (Tampa, FL)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;~20 hrs/week | $40–$45/hr | Remote with occasional on-site days at our Tampa (Channelside) office&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;We&#39;re a fast-moving, entrepreneurial PR agency looking for an experienced EA to support an executive at our company. You&#39;ll keep their calendar, travel, meetings, and priorities running smoothly so they can focus on growing the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The setup&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Roughly 20 hours/week at $40–$45/hr, mostly remote&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Occasional on-site days at our Channelside office — you&#39;ll need to be in the Tampa area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Time-sensitive items sometimes pop up outside business hours; we&#39;re looking for someone responsive when it counts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Potential to grow into supporting additional executives (and more hours) over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Own the executive&#39;s calendar, scheduling, and travel end to end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Prep them for meetings: research, documents, presentations, logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Handle expenses and confidential corporate and financial information with discretion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Track follow-ups and keep deadlines from slipping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Use AI tools to automate the repetitive tasks and streamline workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Occasional in-person office tasks and errands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;3+ years supporting executives or C-suite leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Meticulous organization, polished communication, calm under shifting priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Strong Microsoft Offic

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GEO &amp;amp; PR Coordinator (Generative Engine Optimization)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Miami, FL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a GEO &amp;amp; PR Coordinator to join 5W&#39;s content team and grow our presence — and the presence of our AI Visibility Index research — across both traditional search and AI-powered answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, and Gemini. This is a hands-on role for someone with a couple years of experience creating content across formats (written, video, social) who&#39;s excited to help get our research picked up by media outlets and cited by AI engines alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of content, PR, and AI search, and it&#39;s built for someone who already lives in AI tools day-to-day, not someone learning them for the first time. You&#39;ll use AI not just to optimize &lt;em&gt;for&lt;/em&gt; AI search engines, but as a core part of how you work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Content Creation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write blog posts, articles, FAQs, and web copy optimized for both readers and AI answer engines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create short-form video content (Reels, TikToks, YouTube Shorts) that supports brand visibility and repurposes into written content (and vice versa)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage a social content calendar, adapting core content into platform-specific formats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Script, film, and edit video content with minimal oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build hub and cluster content around the AI Visibility Index and related research, designed to move brand marketers to contact 5W&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure content in clear, answer-first formats (direct answers up top, scannable headers, lists, tables) that AI models can easily parse and cite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools (ChatGPT, Claude, Lovable, etc.) daily to speed up research, drafting, editing, and light prototyping — e.g., building quick interactive pages or visualizations to accompany studies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Relations &amp;amp; Media Outreach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the pitching of the AI Visibility Index and other proprietary studies, data, and reports to relevant media outlets and journalists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain media lists/contacts relevant to our industry and study topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write pitch emails, press releases, and media one-pagers summarizing key study findings, meeting 5W&#39;s sourcing and verification standards as a baseline expectation on every piece&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Package studies with visuals, sourceable data, and quotable stats that make them easy for reporters to cite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage follow-up communication with journalists and fulfill media requests (data, quotes, interviews)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clear line from each placement to any resulting inbound inquiry, so leadership can see what earned media is producing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GEO &amp;amp; SEO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct keyword and topic research to inform content planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement on-page SEO (titles, meta descriptions, alt text, internal linking)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow 5W&#39;s presence and citations in AI-generated answers, tracked through Profound and Otterly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support structured data/schema implementation in collaboration with the SEO &amp;amp; GEO Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor brand mentions and citations across both AI responses and media coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Performance &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and analyze performance data from tools like Google Search Console, GA4, Ahrefs/Semr

